quran[7]{c,v,t,f}:
  37,1,"By those (angels) ranged in ranks (or rows)."
  37,2,"By those (angels) who drive the clouds in a good way."
  37,3,"By those (angels) who bring the Book and the Qur’ân from Allâh to mankind [Tafsir Ibn Kathîr]."
  37,4,"Verily your Ilâh (God) is indeed One (i.e. Allâh):"
  37,5,"Lord of the heavens and of the earth, and all that is between them, and Lord of every point of the sun’s risings.<sup foot_note=154834>1</sup>",footnotes:154834:1
  37,6,"Verily We have adorned the near heaven with the stars (for beauty).<sup foot_note=154835>1</sup>",footnotes:154835:1
  37,7,"And to guard against every rebellious devil."
  37,8,"They cannot listen to the higher group (angels) for they are pelted from every side."
  37,9,"Outcast, and theirs is a constant (or painful) torment."
  37,10,"Except such as snatch away something by stealing, and they are pursued by a flaming fire of piercing brightness."